TEN random things about me.
1. I don't like to wear shoes around the house.
2. I am so going to need therapy. ( like jessica said)
3. I like to stand in the rain.
4. I am a serious homebody.
5. I love to dance, even if it isn't well.
6. I'm more insecure than you might think.
7. I'm not open outright, but if you ask I will tell you.
8. I 'm really sensitive/emotional.
9. I do things on purpose sometimes just to see peoples' reactions.
10. I get really lonely sometimes. 

NINE ways to win my heart.
1. Make me laugh. 
2. Accept me for who I am.
3. Be honest.
4. Don't be afraid that I will judge you.
5. If there is something you want to say just say it.
6. Show affection, but not in the creepy, gross way.
7. Be considerate.
8. Love me but not in the obsessive way.
9. Surprise me.

EIGHT things I want to do before I die.
1. Find love. 
2. Visit Belgium. 
3. Travel the world.
4. Have a home of my own.
5. Have fun.
6. Learn to do Latin Ballroom dancing.
7. Learn to make clothing.
8. Become fleunt in French.

SEVEN ways to annoy me. 
1. Tell me information that you think I don't know or need to know.
2. Ignore me
3. Do that lalala I'm not listening thing or tell me to shut up repeatedly
4. Say like more than twice in a sentence.
5. Be close minded
6. Not be there for me
7. Dissappoint me

SIX things I believe in.
1. Myself 
2. My friends and family
3. Karma
4. Love
5. Reincarnation
6. The ability to change

FIVE things I'm afraid of.
1. Worms/millipedes
2. Heights
3. Not meeting my own expectations
4. Not finding love
5. Rejection

FOUR things I'm thankful for
1. My family
2. My Friends
3. My life
4. Surviving Katrina

THREE ways to describe myself
1. Observant
2. Goofy
3. Unique

TWO things I want right now
1. Less stress
2. Clarity

ONE person... thing.... I want to see right now
1. My dad's house like it was.....

I'm glad that high school isn't going to last much longer so that I don't have to deal with petty things such as whether black and brown match and because I don't think I could take the stress much longer. Breaking down and crying in 5th period today was enough of a wake up call. I'm just plain frustrated, overworked, and exhausted and the bad part is it is all my own fault.

Ummm so yeah I'm one of the newspaper staff editors now. I'm not sure what I have gotten myself into, but oh well. I had a pretty good weekend. I went to the Peter Anderson Art Festival. There was a lot of really neat things and I wish that I had money and room for stuff like that. My dad and I went to see the Legend of Zorro. I thought it was really awesome and funny. Just thought I'd give a little update.
A dress or pants for homecoming.....what to choose, what to choose...

AAAAHHHH..............!!!!!

Sorry needed to vent......

So I guess I should make and update. School work is trying to kick my butt, I'm doing my best, though. Outside of school everything is hectic, but livable. I wonder more about my family more and more. I love them but man..... As bad as it may sound my grandparents left town today to go to Texas and we are all very thankful. We might actually have a nice, fun night. We plan on going to the movies. Other than that I don't know what to say. Later......

I just got internet back today. I hope everyone I know and more are blessed enough to have the comforts that I am beginning to gain back myself. Hope to hear from many people soon and guess I will see you all back at school those who are still there.

Samantha and I survived the game. Anna went with us, so it was not too bad. I think I understood the game fairly well, Samantha didn't pay attention to it too much I think. We hung out with Christine and Scarlett during the 3rd quarter. We watched Jessica look bored at the sidelines. It was an interesting experience there are way too many people there most of which just socialize. It wasn't a horrible, but I wouldn't waste my time with it often.

Samantha and I are going to tonight's football game. <FONT size=4>It's a shocker I know.</FONT> Just typing that is weird. We are going as support and mostly to just hang out afterward. I shall have to update later this weekend to document how traumatizing it might be. Just thought I would share that info. so just in case weird events begin to occur signaling the end of the world or anything like that it's our fault.

I'm sorry if I seem inattentive or anything of the like now a days. I just have a lot to keep up with. I try to read everyone's journal when I can and attempt to stay current with everyone's affairs. My internet is bad, though, and I have a big amount of responsibilities, but I care about all of my friends and shall do my best to be social.

School is good. My schedule is great and I have lots of people in my classes which is very nice. It is going to be a hard year but oh well.

I just got back from Kissimmee, FL yesterday. Disney was fun. My dad and I went to Epcot and MGM Studios. Being around my grandmother wasn't a ball, but hey she is related to me I suppose. I have about a week and a half to get my act together for school. I know I will be a senior this year but I don't wanna go back. Blah...see you all soon if not before school.

hmm I wonder....is this truthful?

It's been awhile, I know. I really don't ever have much to say unless I'm ranting or something else along those lines. I worked for the first time at my new job Saturday. I have to wear black dress pants, a white button up long sleeve shirt, vest, and tie. I look like a penguin and feel completely unlike myself but its a part time job that makes good money so I will not complain. Washingtone D.C. was a change of pace for me. It was busy and way too much to handle while being really beautiful to look at or at least Mount Vernon was. I have many side projects to work on which I seem to have no energy for, oh well.

---- My mom and Hugh are driving each other insane. Mom wants a divorce because he is a jerk. I have no problem with what she wants but if they get divorced life will be a bit different for me.  We shall see what develops.

I hope everyone's summer is awesome....... later...

This has been a surprisingly busy week for me. I have had a lot going on and I don't think it is going to let up very much anytime soon. My mom had her last surgery this week and is now home. Her back is still hurting her a bit but hopefully she fully recovers soon. Until then I'm the designated responsible one in the house I suppose. Umm...really don't know what else to say. Hope everyone has a Great summer!

This whole being social and taking part in things is exhausting. Sheesh. Um let's see my life lately has consisted of homework and other stuff that I'm trying to dedicate myself too. It's interesting. Today in 5th period was crazy. We didn't have to do anything and most of the class was hyper. It was a new twist on the insanity which was already that class. Oh well....Samantha and I are going to be working at one of the car washes tomorrow if it doesn't rain. Tell people about it if they need to wash their cars. :) later all...

My mom and Hugh were not here when I woke. Obviously, they had put the dogs in the backyard until I woke up to let them in. Well, I wake up, go to let the dogs in and oh dear there is one missing. So, guess who got to walk around the whole neighborhood calling out his name. And once again this stresses my mom out because it's her dog. But it is my responsibility to find him... grrrr stupid teenager boy dog....

Well.. I thought I might update my journal. I get to play nurse this weekend. Heh, no outfit so don't get any ideas anyone. I dread finishing my critical analysis but what must be done will be. Umm... I don't have to sell anymore stuff for prom, unless I'm needed I suppose but hopefully not. Let's see what else...oh I have to get serious about raising money for the history day trip. There isn't too much else to mention hope everyone has a good weekend. Later....
I think computers hate me. I don't know if that's paranoia on my part or what. Oh well...I don't like them either so it's mutual.

Your dominant element is earth. Even if you sometimes pretend otherwise, do you kind of like hanging out with your folks or siblings? The ancient Yin-Yang scholars saw earth types as pretty family-oriented. Also, they are generally trusted by their friends and, being very reliable and responsible, rarely disappoint them. Earth people like to invite friends over for low-key activities like watching movies or just to hang out. 
Do you have a fairly stable temper? It's not easy getting Earth types worked up. 

Even if you grab a handful of earth and throw it up in the air it will always settle back to the ground. The element earth is therefore related to stability. 

Trustworthiness is the dominant feature of the elemental energy of earth. This promotes the loyalty and responsibility in us. 

If it isn't disturbed, earth can be very stationary. The earth element therefore allows us to sit still for a while and not to change our mind too often. 

Things that provide security will encourage the positive qualities of earth. Everything from a sturdy bag to a well-built house can fulfill the need for safety. 

A humid climate is best for earth as it keeps the earth damp and stops it from getting blown away. The colors that correspond to it are yellow and brown. 

Earth types are known for having a sweet tooth. 

NOTE: Earth types look huggable. They tend to have full cheeks and a generous mouth.

She asked him if he would want to be with her forever....and he said
no..
She then asked him if she were to leave would he cry, and once again he
replied with a no.
She had heard enough.
  As she walked away, tears streaming down her face the boy grabbed her
arm and said....
You're not pretty you're beautiful.
I dont want to be with you forever. I NEED to be with you forever.
And I wouldnt cry if you walked away...I'd die..
